-- UniCredit Shareholder CassaMarca Says `No Plot' in Profumo's Resignation
-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t   a n d   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 2010-09-24T08:10:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/unicredit-shareholder-says-no-plot-in-profumo-resignation.html
UniCredit SpA shareholder
Fondazione CassaMarca said that there was “no plot” in the
resignation of Chief Executive Officer Alessandro Profumo. The
decision was driven by Chairman Dieter Rampl,"a higly valid
individual,’’ the foundation’s Chairman Dino De Poli said in e-
mailed statement today.  CassaMarca said that there was “no political influence”
on the decision. De Poli also defended the role of foundations
in the Italian banking system in a letter to Assisurazioni
Generali SpA Chairman’s Cesare Geronzi. The banking foundation
owns 0.8 percent of UniCredit.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tommaso Ebhardt at 
 tebhardt@bloomberg.net  